President Cyril Ramaphosa is set to address Parliament on Wednesday on gender-based violence. CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa has announced an emergency action plan to address gender-based violence in the country. Ramaphosa was addressing a joint sitting of the National Assembly and the National Council of Province on steps the government is taking in response to the scourge of gender-based violence The president also said additional funding has been allocated to fight gender-based violence. Here are Ramaphosa’s top 10 quotes from his address on Thursday. 